Bootstrap: docker
From: nvcr.io/nvidia/pytorch:24.10-py3

%labels
    Project    compilAR (Cornell Data Science)
    Purpose    Build/run environment for the StragglAR allreduce compiler
    BaseImage  nvcr.io/nvidia/pytorch:24.10-py3

%help
    Toolchain image for the StragglAR project.
    Provides CUDA, nvcc, NCCL, OpenMPI, UCX, Python 3, PyTorch, and numpy.

    The project source is NOT baked in. Apptainer auto-bind-mounts the host
    CWD into the container at the same path, so source edits are visible
    immediately without a rebuild.

    Typical usage, run from the repo root:
        apptainer exec --nv compilAR.sif python3 stragglar/compilAR.py <schedule.txt> <out.cu>
        apptainer exec --nv compilAR.sif nvcc -ccbin mpicxx -arch=sm_XX <out.cu> -lnccl -lmpi -o <bin>
        apptainer exec --nv compilAR.sif ./stragglar/launch.sh <N> <bin> <args...>

    Replace sm_XX with the compute capability of your target GPU
    (nvidia-smi --query-gpu=compute_cap --format=csv,noheader).

%test
    # Aborts the build if any of these fail. Catches "image built but broken".
    set -e
    nvcc --version
    mpirun --version | head -1
    python3 -c "import torch, numpy; print(f'torch={torch.__version__}  numpy={numpy.__version__}')"

%runscript
    exec "$@"
